headline: Big Bank stocks sell off on earnings: A look at smaller banks
summary: Bank stocks Wells Fargo (WFC), Citigroup (C), and Bank of America (BAC) are selling off on Wednesday after the companies released their fourth quarter earnings results. JPMorgan Chase stock (JPM) continues to slide since reporting its earnings on Tuesday. Whalen Global Advisors Chairman Chris Whalen sits down with Market Catalysts Host Julie Hyman to examine what may be causing these declines in bank stocks.
